<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1325,1346,1892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Male genitalia. Distiphallus approximately same length as mesophallus. Tubules parallel sided and diverging in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[750,837,1386,1412]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 17" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1201,1225]" captionTargetBox="[376,1216,695,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[371,1228,685,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 17. Cerodontha (Dizygomyza) scirpioides Zlobin. 13, phallus ventral view; 14, phallus lateral view; 15, epandrium with surstylus (ventral, left) 16, epandrium lateral view showing anal projection (ap); 17, ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[805,837,1386,1412]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with a row of small to moderately long spines anteriorly and 
<number box="[670,685,1426,1452]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
long but weak bristles on lower margin (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1308,1426,1452]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 17" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1201,1225]" captionTargetBox="[376,1216,695,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[371,1228,685,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 17. Cerodontha (Dizygomyza) scirpioides Zlobin. 13, phallus ventral view; 14, phallus lateral view; 15, epandrium with surstylus (ventral, left) 16, epandrium lateral view showing anal projection (ap); 17, ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1308,1426,1452]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium with patch of medial posteroventral spines (
<figureCitation box="[922,1010,1466,1492]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 17" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1201,1225]" captionTargetBox="[376,1216,695,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[371,1228,685,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 17. Cerodontha (Dizygomyza) scirpioides Zlobin. 13, phallus ventral view; 14, phallus lateral view; 15, epandrium with surstylus (ventral, left) 16, epandrium lateral view showing anal projection (ap); 17, ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[978,1010,1466,1492]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal projection of epandrium prominent (
<figureCitation box="[478,566,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 17" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1201,1225]" captionTargetBox="[376,1216,695,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[371,1228,685,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 17. Cerodontha (Dizygomyza) scirpioides Zlobin. 13, phallus ventral view; 14, phallus lateral view; 15, epandrium with surstylus (ventral, left) 16, epandrium lateral view showing anal projection (ap); 17, ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[533,566,1506,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme not greatly enlarged (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1180,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 17" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1201,1225]" captionTargetBox="[376,1216,695,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[371,1228,685,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 17. Cerodontha (Dizygomyza) scirpioides Zlobin. 13, phallus ventral view; 14, phallus lateral view; 15, epandrium with surstylus (ventral, left) 16, epandrium lateral view showing anal projection (ap); 17, ejaculatory apodeme." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1148,1180,1506,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1325,1346,1892]" lastBlockId="7.[264,1323,284,390]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Comments. This species is easily distinguished from other Nearctic species by the presence of one strong upper 
<emphasis box="[612,650,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ors</emphasis>
and one much reduced lower 
<emphasis box="[1006,1043,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ors</emphasis>
. The species was originally described from Durango, 
<collectingCountry box="[660,753,1626,1652]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Additional specimens from Chiapas, 
<collectingCountry box="[1235,1325,1626,1652]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[272,394,1666,1692]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">MEXICO</collectingCountry>
: Chiapas, San Critobal 
<number box="[670,736,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7000.0">7000</number>
’, 
<date box="[754,872,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1969-05-15">
<number box="[754,783,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="15.0">15</number>
.v. 
<number box="[807,872,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</date>
, H.J.Teskey, 
<specimenCount box="[1027,1133,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="female">
<number box="[1027,1042,1666,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
female
</specimenCount>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1145,1207,1666,1692]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/y2kv-9w3k" name="Canadian National Collection of Insects, Arachnids, and Nematodes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">CNC</collectionCode>
) and Cartago, 
<collectingCountry box="[334,466,1706,1732]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[485,668,1706,1732]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">COSTA RICA</collectingCountry>
: Cartago, Dulce Nombre, Vivero Linda Vista 
<quantity box="[1236,1320,1706,1732]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400m</quantity>
, Malaise trap, 
<date box="[431,577,1746,1772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1993-06" valueMax="1993-08-31" valueMin="1993-06-00">
vi–viii. 
<number box="[517,577,1746,1772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</date>
, P. Hanson, 
<specimenCount box="[731,816,1746,1772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="male">
<number box="[731,746,1746,1772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
male
</specimenCount>
, LEM) on which the above description is based apparently belong to this species. Although there are slight differences in external characteristics (gena height relative to eye height, wing length, color of calypter and fringe) and shape of genitalia of these specimens (distiphallus not as dilated in lateral view, and generally narrower, parallel sided in ventral view), these specimens are placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Cerodontha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scirpioides" subGenus="Dizygomyza">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. (D.) scirpioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until more specimens become available to confirm possible variation of the species.
</paragraph>
